 If you can't beat them, join them.
 At least that seems to be AT and T's thinking.
 Ma bell is asking the baby bells to sell its long distance service, in an
 arrangement similar to the one that upstart carrier Quest has worked out with
 US West and Ameritech, two of the baby bells.
 Just last week, AT and T and other long distance carriers sued to stop those
 deals on grounds that the baby bells had not yet opened their local phone
 markets to competition.
